  "local_port": 53992,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the entry requirements for the University of Melbourne?",
  "response": "The **University of Melbourne** is one of Australia's leading universities, renowned for its high academic standards and diverse range of programs. Entry requirements can vary depending on the level of study (undergraduate or postgraduate), the specific course or faculty, and whether you are a domestic or international applicant. Below is a general overview of the typical entry requirements:\n\n---\n\n### **Undergraduate Admission Requirements**\n\n1. **Academic Qualifications:**\n   - **Australian Students:** Completion of the **Australian Year 12** with results meeting the specific score requirements for the chosen course.\n   - **International Students:** Equivalent qualifications such as **A-Levels**, **International Baccalaureate (IB)**, or other recognized pre-university programs. Each course may have specific subject prerequisites and minimum score requirements.\n\n2. **English Language Proficiency:**\n   - Non-native English speakers must demonstrate proficiency through standardized tests:\n     - **IELTS:** Minimum score usually around 6.5 overall with no band below 6.0.\n     - **TOEFL iBT:** Typically a minimum of 79 overall with specific section scores.\n     - **Pearson PTE Academic:** Often a minimum score of 58 overall.\n     - *Note:* Specific courses, especially those in health sciences or law, may require higher scores.\n\n3. **Prerequisite Subjects:**\n   - Certain courses demand specific subjects or higher-level math, science, or other disciplines. For example, engineering programs might require prerequisite courses in mathematics and physics.\n\n4. **Supplementary Requirements:**\n   - Some courses may require portfolios (e.g., Art and Design), auditions (e.g., Performing Arts), or interviews.\n\n5. **ATAR Score (for Australian Students):**\n   - The **Australian Tertiary Admission Rank (ATAR)** is used for most undergraduate admissions in Australia. Competitive courses may require higher ATAR scores.\n\n---\n\n### **Postgraduate Admission Requirements**\n\n1. **Academic Qualifications:**\n   - A relevant **Bachelor\u2019s degree** with a specified minimum grade point (often equivalent to a Honours degree or a certain GPA, depending on the program and country of the undergraduate degree).\n\n2. **Relevant Experience:**\n   - Some postgraduate programs, especially professional ones like **MBA** or **Master of Social Work**, may require relevant work experience.\n\n3. **English Language Proficiency:**\n   - Similar to undergraduate requirements, with possible higher minimum scores for competitive programs.\n\n4. **Additional Requirements:**\n   - **Statement of Purpose (SOP):** Outlining your reasons for applying and career goals.\n   - **Letters of Recommendation:** Typically 2-3 references from academic or professional sources.\n   - **Curriculum Vitae (CV):** Detailing your academic and professional background.\n   - **Portfolios or Research Proposals:** For certain specialized courses or research degrees.\n\n---\n\n### **Application Process**\n\n1. **Choose Your Course:**\n   - Explore the **[University of Melbourne's course offerings](https://study.unimelb.edu.au/)** to find programs that align with your academic and career goals.\n\n2. **Check Specific Requirements:**\n   - Each course may have unique prerequisites or additional criteria. Always refer to the specific course page for detailed information.\n\n3. **Submit Your Application:**\n   - **Australian Students:** Apply through **State/Territory Tertiary Admissions Centre (e.g., VTAC, UAC)**.\n   - **International Students:** Apply directly through the **University of Melbourne's online application portal** or via authorized agents.\n\n4. **Provide Supporting Documents:**\n   - Ensure all required documentation (transcripts, language test scores, IDs) are submitted by the deadlines.\n\n5. **Receive Offer and Accept:**\n   - If admitted, follow the university's instructions to accept your offer and enroll in your courses.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Deadlines:** Be mindful of application deadlines, which can vary by course and applicant type (domestic vs. international).\n- **Scholarships:** Explore scholarship opportunities that can provide financial assistance based on merit or need.\n- **Contact Admissions:** If you have specific questions or need clarification, reach out to the **[University of Melbourne Admissions Office](https://study.unimelb.edu.au/how-to-apply/admissions)** for personalized guidance.\n\n---\n\n### **Useful Links**\n\n- [University of Melbourne Official Website](https://www.unimelb.edu.au/)\n- [Undergraduate Admission Requirements](https://study.unimelb.edu.au/find/courses/undergraduate)\n- [Postgraduate Admission Requirements](https://study.unimelb.edu.au/find/courses/postgraduate)\n- [English Language Requirements](https://study.unimelb.edu.au/how-to-apply/english-language-requirements)\n\n---\n\n**Note:** Admission requirements are subject to change. It's essential to consult the **University of Melbourne\u2019s official website** or contact their admissions office directly for the most current and detailed information tailored to your specific circumstances.",
